net.markenwerk.commons.collections.sequences

Interface Sequence<Payload>

  • Type Parameters:
    Payload - The payload type
    All Superinterfaces:
    BidirectionalIterable<Payload>, IndexedSource<Payload>, Iterable<Payload>, ProtectedBidirectionalIterable<Payload>, ProtectedIterable<Payload>, Source<Payload>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractListSequence, AbstractSequence, ListSequence

    public interface Sequence<Payload>
extends IndexedSource<Payload>
    A Sequence is a linear data structure.
    Since:
    1.0.0
    Author:
    Torsten Krause (tk at markenwerk dot net)

      • hashCode

        int hashCode()
        Returns the hash code of this Sequence.

        The hash code of a Sequence is defined to be the result of the following calculation: 

         int hashCode = 1;
 Iterator<Payload> iterator = sequence.iterator();
 while (iterator.hasNext()) {
        Payload payload = iterator.next();
        hashCode = 31 * hashCode + (null == payload ? 0 : payload.hashCode());
 }
        Overrides:
        hashCode in class Object
        Returns:
        The hash code of this Sequence.

      • equals

        boolean equals(Object object)
        Compares the given object with this Sequence for equality.

        Returns true if and only if the given object is also a Sequence, both Sequences have the same size, and all corresponding pairs of elements in the two Sequences are equal.

        Overrides:
        equals in class Object
        Parameters:
        object - The object to be used.
        Returns:
        If the given object is equal to this Sequence.
